The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Tuesday, February 10, 2004  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 Veteran sports journalist and immensely popular radio commentator Ajoy Bose died in a city hospital on Monday. He was 84 and is survived by his wife and daughter. He was suffering for a long time and had been hospitalised with a respiratory problem.				 																																																	A former sports editor of Bengali daily Basumati, Bose was known for his unique commentary style, which made him popular. He was associated with the All India Radio for a long time.				 																																																	His body was taken to the AIR office, CAB and IFA. Among many who expressed grief at Boses death was chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee. He was cremated at the Kashi Mitra Ghat crematorium.				 																																																	 Mohun Bagan will kick off their conditioning camp for the second phase of the NFL on Wednesday at the SAI Eastern Centre. Four Punjab players  Hardip Gill, Harpreet Singh, Hardip Saini and Sanjeev Maria  rejoined the teams practice on Monday. 				 																																																	 Howrah beat South 24 Parganas 1-0 in the Konark Sheets state league match, Biswajit Neur scoring the winner. Hoogly, Chandannagar and Bardhaman have already entered the semi-finals.				 																																																	 The 17th all India postal football tournament will be held at SAI Eastern Centre from Thursday to Monday. Announcing this on Monday, P.K. Chatterjee, chairman, department of posts (West Bengal circle), said eleven teams from various circles will take part in the meet. 				 																																																	 RPG and JSR amp; Co. won their matches on Monday in the mercantile mixed basketball, being held at the Rangers Club. While RPG overcame Tata Tea 37-23, JSR amp; Co. beat TCS 35-12. 				 																																																	FOOTBALL: Inter-school meet final: Kodalia Prasanna Banga HS vs Vivekananda Palli Kishorbharati HS at Bidhannagar Sports Complex from 1.30p.m.				 																																																	GOLF: All-India amateur meet at RCGC.
